CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 20, 1958, pg. A9 reads: "Hibiscus Club Entertains - The Hibiscus Neighborhood Club gave its annual Christmas party at the home of Mrs. E. McKenzie, president. Mrs. C. Johnson was chairman.  Seated, left to right, are Mrs. Mary Davis, Mrs. Ossic Aughry, Mrs. Adellar Yarbrough, Mrs. Gertrude Stevens, baby Shelly Hall and Mrs. Georgianna Briscoe.  Standing: Mmes. Jennie Cissell, Charlie Johnson, Murdies Brown, Channie Thomas, Fannie White, Mr. Willie L. Yarbrough, Mrs. Elizabeth McKenzie, M.W. Edison, Mmes. Daisy Barnett, Corkie Williams and Rachel Washington. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of members of the Hibiscus Neighborhood Club, seated, left to right: Mary Davis, Ossic Aughry, Adellar Yarbrough, Gertrude Stevens, baby Shelly Hall, and Georgianna Briscoe; standing: Jennie Cissell, Charlie Johnson, Murdies Brown, Channie Thomas, Fannie White, Willie L. Yarbrough, Elizabeth McKenzie, M.W. Edison, Daisy Barnett, Corkie Williams, and Rachel Washington, gathered around table for Christmas party in home of Elizabeth McKenzie
